data.title: Great food, great atmosphere
data.text: My family and I are regulars. Big fan of the Green Enchiladas dinner. There's a wide array of options on the menu and it's one of the better Mexican joints in the NMB, Aventura, Hollywood area. I've had better tacos, but the overall menu is great.

data.title: Feel welcome for once
data.text:
Two weeks ago I went once more to this local restaurant, and as always, as soon as i sat down, the waitress brought me warm chips and salsa, without me even ask for anything...
There are plenty of restaurants in the area but this one stands out in this matter, and keeps me choosing it over the others. The feeling of being welcome to a business is something rare now days and that's why I decided to reward it with a very good review.
I want visitors and locals to discover this "feel like among friends" place.
Now, the food is as good as the feeling. Love the place.

data.title: Another average Mexican restaurant
data.text: I have not found anything on the menu to rave about. While the food is good enough to be rated as okay. I am unable to say that you will have a spectacular meal. The environment is pleasing and pleasant. The staff is professional but not very friendly.

data.title: Lunch
data.text: My husband and I stopped in for lunch on Sunday afternoon. Never being there before we didn't know what to expect.  However, the place was nicely decorated with bright colors and televisions in place for sports fans.  We split a Mexican shrimp cocktail that could've been a meal in and of itself. The shrimp were cooked perfectly and the tomato juice with avocado, cilantro, onion with a little heat was great.  My husband had the La Roqueta burrito with pork and I had the Hot & Spicy burrito. My husband's dish consisted of two burritos stuffed with well seasoned pork and rice covered with a tomatillo sauce served with rice and beans.  My big burrito was stuffed with rice, beans and spicy shredded chicken, topped with spicy chunks of beef and that amazing tomatillo sauce. Needless to say, we both took half of our entrees home and I got the night off of cooking. Overall a great place and we can't wait to go for Taco Tuesday.

data.title: Great salsa! Good overall food!
data.text: Chips and salsa area  staple at any Mexican restaurant; but the salsa here is one of our favorites ever. Our group ordered typical fare: tacos, fajitas, burritos...all were good and typical for this type of place but we thoroughly enjoyed it all. The area around the restaurant is a little sketchy but you can walk around to the shops. The area looks like it needs a facelift; but the restaurant was fine.

data.title: Great food.
data.text: Great place to eat and enjoy time with family and friends. Marcelo Osorio very gentle and wonderful attention to us.

data.title: Food good, service / hospitality not so much
data.text: Used a Groupon we had purchased so we notified our waiter who started spitting out the regs for using the Groupon. Food was good but compared to other restaurants we visited while vacationing in the area I found them overpriced.

data.title: Favorite place!!!
data.text: Our favorite local Mexican restaurant.  Great margaritas and good food.  The authentic Mexican dishes in the clay potS are fantastic.  We haven't had the tacos and burritos.  Orale corn is a must try.  Staff has always been friendly.

data.title: Delicious spot !!
data.text: Ive lived in Hollywood my whole life and I feel so sad to have just found this place. The atmosphere is very nice, the food is fantastic and the prices are comparable to most restaurants like it. With so many options for different food in downtown Hollywood there's really no reason I can see you shouldn't check this place out!! (:

data.title: Authentic Mexican
data.text: Living here 20 years the first 15 we had an authentic place where they seen my kids grow up. They closed and here's come this place. We've dined here 20+ times since they opened and never had a bad meal. This is about as good as it gets in Hollywood.

data.title: Some disappointed whit the prices
data.text: Well the food is good, I think everyone said it if you were in this place. The problem is the overprice. My bill was 64 for two regulars foods and two margaritas. I saw some reviews and the cost was for one big margarita  $9 but really in the place is $12.50 whitout taxes... Oh ! In the menu doesn't appears the price for cocktails. They added 18% for gratuities like 8 dollars more so I was disappointed whit It. I had one groupon for $30 dollars and I must paid 35$ dollars more, really disappointed. Like I said the food is good, just that,  but $65 for some old place whit a regular Mexican food is a joke

data.title: Authentic Mexican
data.text: The food is usually very good. The service is relatively good. On a few occasions I saw a roach either on the wall or on the table. I told the manager and he assured me that they fumigate regularly. I got drink tickets for my troubles. I wish I could give more starts because the food is usually really good.

data.title: First time visit and maybe last
data.text: I went to this place with a friend.I love Mexican and i was excited.My favorite are the re fried beans and i was excited to try it there.I was disappointed!I have ordered Fajita(which is my favorite Mexican dish) and my shrimps were stuck to the bottom of the plate.We had few drinks and when we asked for the check,my friend had a Groupon coupon.The waiter brought the bill and surprise-they included gratuity 18% on the check.My friend asked him why is that as she is a regular there and she never had gratuity added to her check.The answer was they do it all the time.I don't think i will go there again!

data.title: Closest to Authentic!
data.text: I really enjoyed the food here, and will be back.  This to me has been the best tasting Mexican food I have ever had in Broward county.  It did seem like they were short staffed and I had to wait a little to long for a bottled beer.  They do have a large menu so there is a lot to choose from.  I finally had spicy Mexican food!! Portions are large and the price on some items are very reasonable.  Indoor and outdoor patio seating as well.

data.title: Favorite place!!!
data.text: Our favorite local Mexican restaurant.  Great margaritas and good food.  The authentic Mexican dishes in the clay potS are fantastic.  We haven't had the tacos and burritos.  Orale corn is a must try.  Staff has always been friendly.

data.title: Worst Service Ever
data.text: Worst service ever experienced from any restaurant. Waitress was a complete idiot and the manager was worst. Visited with a groupon. Waitress poorly communicated the drink special then proceeded to verbally insult us in Spanish. The manager was worst. Instead of dealing with it professionally she called the police. Great management. Great service. Great experience. NOT! Wouldn't send my worst enemy here. Avoid at all cost. And the food was not worth the headache. I've had a lot better at better prices.

data.title: Unprofessional staff
data.text:
Been to orale...enjoy the food. This was my 4th time there. We had a Groupon. 60$ towards food. We knew we would exceed this amount. We informed waitress about the Groupon and she proceeded to tell us 3$ maragritas for happy hour. We ordered food and margaritas. When we get the bill we exceeded groupon by 35$. A closer look at the bill showed the margaritas were charged as 6$ each.  We called the waitress over who informed us that we could not take advantage of happy hour because we used a Groupon and 2 promotions cannot be used at once. We explained she never told us this. She got the manager who explained the same
We said we understood but that that's not what the waitress told us. She called the waitress over. Meanwhile they barely speak English..thankfully our group had a Spanish speaking person in it. Manager was very rude and allowed the waitress to curse at us and tell us we were miserable and such. As we were discussing amonst ourselves that we should just pay the bill and go..we were getting our money ready, the manager called the cops to say she had customers that would not pay! We left our money and walked out. Sure enough the cops found us a block down. We told him the story and he thought it was ridiculous. We all walked back down to the restaurant and the manager admitted we paid. I would never ever give business to anyone that allows this to escalate like this and allows their employees to curse at the customers.

data.title: END TO MY ANNIVESARY WEEKEND
data.text: After a great anniversary weekend SINDAY - the best lunch ever with a great MICHEALADA .. it was huge.. The food was decent and the service GREAT

data.title: Watch out for the 18% gratuity
data.text:
Went to try Orale on a Groupon after positive comments on TripAdvisor.  The food was nothing special...pretty bland for a Mexican restaurant.  The house special "carnitas" had little flavor.  

Although it was just 2 of us, they socked me with a 18% gratuity for mediocre service (I don't mind tipping even higher for great service).  I paid cash and the waiter "forgot" to bring me the change portion of my bill bringing the total gratuity to over 20%.  Disgusted we left and would never go back. 

If you want great Mexican food, drive a few miles north to Fort Lauderdale and go to Roco's Tocos as it is well worth the trip. 

Skip Orale.  Hasta la vista, Baby.

data.title: Very nice family style Mexican restaurant!
data.text: The place is a classic family style Mexican restaurant but with a full bar. My house Margarita was delicious & just strong enough. My shrimp dish was great & my husband loved his enchiladas. Our waiter was friendly and helpful. We will make this a regular spot when we feel like Mexican food. The prices were very fair for this area & the portions generous.
